You are an expert in TypeScript, Turborepo, pnpm workspaces, Next.js, shared packages, and monorepo architecture.

# Project Type
This is a Turborepo monorepo with pnpm workspaces, containing multiple apps and shared packages.

## Tech Stack
- Turborepo 2.x
- pnpm workspaces
- TypeScript 5+
- Next.js (apps)
- Vite (packages)
- ESLint + Prettier (shared configs)
- Changesets for versioning

## Monorepo Structure

```
apps/
  web/                   # Next.js main web app
    package.json         # { "name": "@acme/web" }
    next.config.mjs
    src/
  docs/                  # Next.js documentation site
  admin/                 # Admin dashboard
packages/
  ui/                    # Shared UI component library
    package.json         # { "name": "@acme/ui" }
    src/
      components/
      index.ts           # Public exports
  config/
    package.json         # { "name": "@acme/config" }
    eslint/
      next.js
      library.js
    tsconfig/
      base.json
      nextjs.json
      react-library.json
  database/              # Shared database package (Prisma)
    package.json         # { "name": "@acme/database" }
    prisma/
      schema.prisma
    src/
      index.ts           # Export prisma client
  api/                   # Shared API types and utilities
    package.json         # { "name": "@acme/api" }
    src/
      types/
      validators/
  auth/                  # Shared auth utilities
    package.json         # { "name": "@acme/auth" }
turbo.json
pnpm-workspace.yaml
package.json             # Root package.json
```

## turbo.json Configuration

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://turbo.build/schema.json",
  "ui": "tui",
  "tasks": {
    "build": {
      "dependsOn": ["^build"],
      "inputs": ["$TURBO_DEFAULT$", ".env*"],
      "outputs": [".next/**", "!.next/cache/**", "dist/**"]
    },
    "dev": {
      "cache": false,
      "persistent": true
    },
    "test": {
      "dependsOn": ["^build"],
      "inputs": ["src/**/*.ts", "src/**/*.tsx", "test/**/*.ts"],
      "outputs": ["coverage/**"]
    },
    "lint": {
      "dependsOn": ["^build"]
    },
    "type-check": {
      "dependsOn": ["^build"]
    },
    "clean": {
      "cache": false
    }
  },
  "globalDotEnv": [".env", ".env.local"]
}
```

## pnpm-workspace.yaml

```yaml
packages:
  - 'apps/*'
  - 'packages/*'
```

## Shared UI Package

```typescript
// packages/ui/package.json
{
  "name": "@acme/ui",
  "version": "0.0.1",
  "main": "./src/index.ts",
  "types": "./src/index.ts",
  "exports": {
    ".": "./src/index.ts",
    "./button": "./src/components/Button/index.ts"
  },
  "scripts": {
    "build": "tsc",
    "type-check": "tsc --noEmit",
    "lint": "eslint ."
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@acme/config": "workspace:*",
    "@types/react": "*",
    "react": "*",
    "typescript": "*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "react": "^18.0.0"
  }
}

// packages/ui/src/components/Button/Button.tsx
import type { ButtonHTMLAttributes, ReactNode } from 'react';
import { cn } from '../../utils/cn';

export interface ButtonProps extends ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost' | 'destructive';
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  children: ReactNode;
  isLoading?: boolean;
}

export function Button({
  variant = 'primary',
  size = 'md',
  children,
  isLoading = false,
  className,
  disabled,
  ...props
}: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md font-medium transition-colors',
        'focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-2',
        {
          'bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700': variant === 'primary',
          'bg-gray-200 text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-300': variant === 'secondary',
          'bg-transparent hover:bg-gray-100': variant === 'ghost',
          'bg-red-600 text-white hover:bg-red-700': variant === 'destructive',
          'h-8 px-3 text-sm': size === 'sm',
          'h-10 px-4': size === 'md',
          'h-12 px-6 text-lg': size === 'lg',
          'opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed': disabled || isLoading,
        },
        className
      )}
      disabled={disabled || isLoading}
      {...props}
    >
      {isLoading ? <span className="mr-2">...</span> : null}
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## Shared Database Package

```typescript
// packages/database/src/index.ts
import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';

const globalForPrisma = globalThis as unknown as {
  prisma: PrismaClient | undefined;
};

export const prisma =
  globalForPrisma.prisma ??
  new PrismaClient({
    log: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development' ? ['query', 'error'] : ['error'],
  });

if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {
  globalForPrisma.prisma = prisma;
}

export * from '@prisma/client';
```

## Shared TypeScript Config

```json
// packages/config/tsconfig/base.json
{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/tsconfig",
  "display": "Default",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true,
    "resolveJsonModule": true,
    "declaration": true,
    "declarationMap": true,
    "sourceMap": true
  }
}

// packages/config/tsconfig/nextjs.json
{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/tsconfig",
  "display": "Next.js",
  "extends": "./base.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "es6",
    "lib": ["dom", "dom.iterable", "esnext"],
    "module": "esnext",
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "allowJs": true,
    "jsx": "preserve",
    "noEmit": true,
    "plugins": [{ "name": "next" }]
  }
}
```

## Shared ESLint Config

```javascript
// packages/config/eslint/library.js
module.exports = {
  extends: [
    'eslint:recommended',
    'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended',
    'prettier',
  ],
  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],
  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',
  rules: {
    '@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any': 'error',
    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],
  },
};
```

## App — Using Shared Packages

```typescript
// apps/web/package.json
{
  "name": "@acme/web",
  "dependencies": {
    "@acme/ui": "workspace:*",
    "@acme/database": "workspace:*",
    "@acme/api": "workspace:*",
    "next": "15.x"
  }
}

// apps/web/src/app/page.tsx
import { Button } from '@acme/ui';
import { prisma } from '@acme/database';

export default async function Home() {
  const users = await prisma.user.findMany({ take: 5 });

  return (
    <main>
      <Button variant="primary">Click me</Button>
      {users.map(user => <p key={user.id}>{user.name}</p>)}
    </main>
  );
}
```

## Changesets Workflow

```bash
# 修改了 packages/ui 后：
pnpm changeset          # 声明版本变更
pnpm changeset version  # 更新版本号
pnpm changeset publish  # 发布到 npm
```

## Common Turborepo Commands

```bash
# 构建所有包
pnpm turbo build

# 仅运行受变更影响的任务（利用缓存）
pnpm turbo build --filter=...[origin/main]

# 只在特定 app 运行
pnpm turbo dev --filter=@acme/web

# 运行 web 及其所有依赖
pnpm turbo build --filter=@acme/web...
```

## Error Handling Patterns

- Each package should export its own error types
- Apps consume and handle errors from packages
- Use Result types or throw named errors

## File Naming Conventions

- Packages: kebab-case names with @org/ scope
- Configs: `[name].json` or `[name].js`
- Exports: `index.ts` as main export

## What Cursor Should Do

- Always use `workspace:*` for internal dependencies
- Export everything through `index.ts` in packages
- Share configs (tsconfig, eslint) from `packages/config`
- Use Turborepo's dependency graph (`^build`) for build ordering
- Generate package.json with proper `name`, `main`, `types`, `exports`
- Suggest `--filter` flags for targeted task running

## What Cursor Should Avoid

- Do NOT import directly from internal package files — use published exports
- Do NOT add package-specific deps to root package.json
- Do NOT skip the `dependsOn: ["^build"]` for tasks that need built packages
- Do NOT use `*` version ranges for workspace packages — use `workspace:*`
- Do NOT duplicate configs — share via `packages/config`
